  {
    name: "Dr. Sarah Kim",
    location: "High Park, Toronto",
    project: "Climate-Resilient Basement Retrofit", 
    content: "After studying Toronto's climate projections, we invested in comprehensive basement climate adaptation. The July 2024 flood proved it was worth every penny - we stayed completely dry while neighbors flooded.",
    rating: 5,
    date: "September 2024",
    verified: true,
    image: "/images/dryspace_excellence.webp",
    profession: "Climate Researcher"
  },
  {
    name: "Mark & Jennifer Santos",
    location: "The Beaches, Toronto",
    project: "Future-Proof Waterproofing System",
    content: "Living near the lake, we're seeing the impacts of climate change firsthand. Dryspace designed a system that can handle not just today's storms, but the predictions for 2040. Smart investment in our future.",
    rating: 5,
    date: "October 2024",
    verified: true, 
    image: "/images/dryspace_excellence.webp",
    focus: "Lake-effect flooding adaptation"
  },
  {
    name: "Roberto Martinez",
    location: "North York, Toronto",
    project: "Smart Climate Monitoring + Waterproofing",
    content: "The IoT monitoring system alerts me to any changes in basement conditions. With Toronto's unpredictable weather, having real-time data and automated responses gives tremendous peace of mind.",
    rating: 5,
    date: "November 2024",
    verified: true,
    image: "/images/dryspace_excellence.webp",
    tech: "Smart home integration"
  }
];

const faqs = [
  {
    category: "Climate Science & Impacts",
    questions: [
      {
        question: "How is climate change specifically affecting Toronto basements?",
        answer: "Toronto is experiencing more intense rainfall (up 15% since 1970s), more freeze-thaw cycles, and higher groundwater levels. The July 16, 2024 storm (97mm in 2 hours) was our 3rd '100-year storm' in just 10 years. These extreme events overwhelm drainage systems and increase hydrostatic pressure against foundations, leading to more frequent and severe basement flooding."
      },
      {
        question: "Why is Canada warming faster than the global average?",
        answer: "Canada is warming at twice the global rate due to Arctic amplification - as ice and snow melt, darker surfaces absorb more heat, accelerating warming. This affects Toronto through: more volatile weather patterns, increased storm intensity, changing precipitation patterns, and more extreme temperature swings that stress building foundations."
      },
      {
        question: "What does '100-year storm' mean if we've had three in 10 years?",
        answer: "A '100-year storm' historically had a 1% chance of occurring in any given year. Climate change has shifted these probabilities - what used to be rare is now becoming common. Toronto now needs to prepare for '100-year storms' happening every 3-5 years instead of once per century. This is why traditional drainage systems are failing."
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    category: "Future Projections & Risks",
    questions: [
      {
        question: "What basement risks will Toronto face by 2030-2050?", 
        answer: "Climate projections show: Annual extreme rainfall events by 2030, +25% winter precipitation by 2050, More frequent freeze-thaw foundation damage, Chronic humidity and mold issues, Potential summer cooling system failures. Without adaptation, basements may become uninhabitable during extreme weather, significantly impacting property values."
      },
      {
        question: "How will changing groundwater levels affect foundations?",
        answer: "Increased precipitation and changing soil moisture patterns will raise groundwater tables. This creates: Higher hydrostatic pressure against foundations, More frequent seepage through concrete, Potential foundation movement and settling, Increased risk of structural damage. Exterior waterproofing becomes critical to handle these new pressure levels."
      },
      {
        question: "Will basement flooding become uninsurable?",
        answer: "Insurance companies are already restricting coverage in high-risk areas. By 2030, we expect: Higher deductibles for flood coverage, Mandatory flood-proofing requirements for coverage, Premium increases in vulnerable neighborhoods, Potential exclusions for repetitive flooding. Proactive waterproofing helps maintain insurability and may reduce premiums."
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    category: "Adaptation Strategies",
    questions: [
      {
        question: "What's the most cost-effective climate adaptation for basements?",
        answer: "Based on cost-benefit analysis: Exterior waterproofing ($12,000-$20,000) prevents the most damage and lasts 25+ years, Enhanced drainage with backup power ($4,500-$11,500) handles extreme rainfall, Smart monitoring systems ($2,000-$5,000) enable early intervention. The combination provides comprehensive protection for about $25,000 - less than the cost of one major flood."
      },
      {
        question: "Should I adapt my basement for current weather or future projections?",
        answer: "Design for 2040 climate projections - it's more cost-effective than retrofitting repeatedly. This means: Sizing drainage for 150mm/hour rainfall (vs. current 50mm/hour standard), Using materials rated for increased humidity, Planning for 2-3x more freeze-thaw cycles, Installing systems that can be upgraded as technology improves."
      },
      {
        question: "How do green infrastructure solutions help with basement flooding?",
        answer: "Green infrastructure reduces flood risk by: Rain gardens absorb 30-40% more runoff than grass, Permeable pavement reduces surface water by 80%, Bioswales slow water flow to sewers, Green roofs reduce building runoff by 50-90%. While these don't directly protect basements, they reduce neighborhood flooding pressure and complement waterproofing systems."
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    category: "Government Support & Programs",
    questions: [
      {
        question: "What government funding is available for basement climate adaptation?",
        answer: "Multiple programs available in 2024-2025: Canada Greener Homes Initiative: Up to $5,000 for waterproofing, Ontario Basement Flooding Protection: Up to $3,400 for drainage, Toronto RainProof Program: $1,200 rebate + free assessment, Federal tax credits: Up to $5,000 for eligible improvements. Total potential support: $10,000-$15,000 for comprehensive projects."
      },
      {
        question: "How is the City of Toronto preparing infrastructure for climate change?",
        answer: "Toronto's climate adaptation includes: $2.5 billion storm sewer upgrades (2020-2030), New developments must handle 100mm/hour rainfall, Green infrastructure requirements for new buildings, Updated flood risk mapping every 5 years, Emergency response improvements. However, existing neighborhoods need private adaptation while waiting for public infrastructure upgrades."
      },
      {
        question: "Will property values be affected by climate adaptation measures?",
        answer: "Climate-adapted homes are increasingly valuable: Flood-protected homes sell for 5-10% premium, Insurance savings add long-term value, Climate resilience becoming a buyer requirement, Unadapted homes may lose value as risks become apparent. Early adaptation protects and enhances property values while later adaptation becomes more expensive as demand increases."
      }
    ]
  }
];
---

<PageLayout title={pageData.title} description={pageData.description}>
  
  <!-- Breadcrumbs -->
  <div class="container mx-auto px-4 mt-4">
    <Breadcrumbs 
      items={[
        { name: "Home", url: "/" },
        { name: "Resources", url: "/resources" },
        { name: "Climate Adaptation" }
      ]}
    />
  </div>

<!-- Climate Hero Section -->
  <section class="climate-hero">
    <div class="hero-container">
      <div class="hero-content">
        <div class="tagline-wrapper">
          <i class="fa-solid fa-earth-americas tagline-icon"></i>
          <span class="tagline">{heroContent.tagline}</span>
          <div class="tagline-line"></div>
        </div>
        
        <h1 class="headline">
          <span class="headline-line">Climate Change</span>
          <span class="headline-line">&</span>
          <span class="headline-line headline-accent">Toronto Basements</span>
        </h1>
        
        <p class="subheadline">{heroContent.subheadline}</p>
        
        <!-- Climate Alert -->
        <div class="climate-alert">
          <div class="alert-icon">
            <i class="fa-solid fa-temperature-high"></i>
          </div>
          <div class="alert-content">
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 uppercase">CANADA'S RAPID WARMING</h3>
            <p>Canada warming at 2x global rate. Toronto +2.8°C by 2050. Extreme weather is the new normal.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Climate Stats -->
        <div class="climate-stats">
          <div class="stat-card warming border-2 border-slate-200">
            <div class="stat-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-temperature-high"></i></div>
            <div class="stat-number">2x</div>
            <div class="stat-label">Canada Warming Rate</div>
            <div class="stat-detail">vs Global Average</div>
          </div>
          <div class="stat-card storms border-2 border-slate-200">
            <div class="stat-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-cloud-bolt"></i></div>
            <div class="stat-number">3rd</div>
            <div class="stat-label">100-Year Storm</div>
            <div class="stat-detail">In Just 10 Years</div>
          </div>
          <div class="stat-card risk border-2 border-slate-200">
            <div class="stat-icon"><i class="fa-solid fa-chart-line-up"></i></div>
            <div class="stat-number">45%</div>
            <div class="stat-label">Flood Risk Increase</div>
            <div class="stat-detail">By 2030</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="hero-actions">
          <button class="btn-primary">
            <i class="fa-solid fa-phone"></i>
            Climate Consultation: 437-545-0067
          </button>
          <button class="btn-secondary">
            <i class="fa-solid fa-download"></i>
            Download Climate Guide
          </button>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="hero-visual">
        <img src="/images/dryspace_exterior_waterproofing_warranty.webp" alt="Climate change impacts on urban infrastructure" class="hero-image" width="800" height="600" loading="lazy" decoding="async">
        <div class="visual-overlay">
          <div class="floating-element temp-rise">
            <i class="fa-solid fa-temperature-high"></i>
            <div>
              <span class="metric">+2.8°C</span>
              <span class="label">By 2050</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="floating-element rainfall-increase">
            <i class="fa-solid fa-cloud-rain"></i>
            <div>
              <span class="metric">+25%</span>
              <span class="label">Rainfall Intensity</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- July 2024 Flood Case Study -->
  <section class="flood-case-study">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold text-slate-900 uppercase">JULY 16, 2024: TORONTO'S CLIMATE REALITY CHECK</h2>
        <p>Analysis of the third "100-year storm" in just 10 years</p>
      </div>

      <div class="case-study-grid">
        <div class="meteorological-data">
          <h3>
            <i class="fa-solid fa-cloud-rain"></i>
            Meteorological Analysis
          </h3>
          <div class="data-points">
            <div class="data-point">
              <span class="label">Duration:</span>
              <span class="value">{july2024FloodDetails.meteorology.duration}</span>
            </div>
            <div class="data-point">
              <span class="label">Total Rainfall:</span>
              <span class="value">{july2024FloodDetails.meteorology.rainfall}</span>
            </div>
            <div class="data-point">
              <span class="label">Peak Intensity:</span>
              <span class="value">{july2024FloodDetails.meteorology.intensity}</span>
            </div>
            <div class="data-point">
              <span class="label">Historical Context:</span>
              <span class="value">{july2024FloodDetails.meteorology.comparison}</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="impact-data">
          <h3>
            <i class="fa-solid fa-house-damage"></i>
            Impact Assessment
          </h3>
          <div class="impact-stats">
            <div class="impact-stat">
              <span class="number">{july2024FloodDetails.impacts.totalDamage}</span>
              <span class="description">in total damage</span>
            </div>
            <div class="impact-stat">
              <span class="number">{july2024FloodDetails.impacts.homesAffected}</span>
              <span class="description">homes affected</span>
            </div>
            <div class="impact-stat">
              <span class="number">{july2024FloodDetails.impacts.emergencyResponses}</span>
              <span class="description">emergency calls</span>
            </div>
            <div class="impact-stat">
              <span class="number">{july2024FloodDetails.impacts.powerOutages}</span>
              <span class="description">lost power</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="lessons-learned">
          <h3>
            <i class="fa-solid fa-lightbulb"></i>
            Key Lessons
          </h3>
          <ul class="lessons-list">
            {july2024FloodDetails.lessons.map((lesson) => (
              <li>
                <i class="fa-solid fa-check-circle"></i>
                {lesson}
              </li>
            ))}
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Recent Extreme Events Timeline -->
  <section class="extreme-events-timeline">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold text-slate-900 uppercase">RECENT EXTREME WEATHER EVENTS</h2>
        <p>Toronto's accelerating pattern of climate impacts</p>
      </div>

      <div class="events-timeline">
        {recentExtremeEvents.map((event, index) => (
          <div class={`event-item ${event.category}`}>
            <div class="event-date">{event.date}</div>
            <div class="event-content">
              <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 uppercase">{event.event}</h3>
              <p class="event-details">{event.details}</p>
              <p class="event-impact">{event.impact}</p>
            </div>
            <div class="event-category">
              <i class={`fa-solid ${
                event.category === 'extreme-rainfall' ? 'fa-cloud-rain' :
                event.category === 'air-quality' ? 'fa-smog' :
                event.category === 'temperature' ? 'fa-temperature-high' :
                'fa-house-flood-water'
              }`}></i>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Future Climate Projections -->
  <section class="climate-projections">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold text-slate-900 uppercase">TORONTO CLIMATE PROJECTIONS 2025-2050</h2>
        <p>Scientific forecasts for planning basement adaptations</p>
      </div>

      <div class="projections-timeline">
        {futureProjections.map((period, index) => (
          <div class="projection-period">
            <div class="period-header">
              <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 uppercase">{period.timeframe}</h3>
              <div class="climate-metrics">
                <div class="metric">
                  <i class="fa-solid fa-temperature-high"></i>
                  <span>{period.temperature}</span>
                </div>
                <div class="metric">
                  <i class="fa-solid fa-cloud-rain"></i>
                  <span>{period.precipitation}</span>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="risks-list">
              <h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 uppercase">KEY BASEMENT RISKS:</h4>
              <ul>
                {period.risks.map((risk) => (
                  <li>
                    <i class="fa-solid fa-triangle-exclamation"></i>
                    {risk}
                  </li>
                ))}
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Adaptation Strategies -->
  <section class="adaptation-strategies">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold text-slate-900 uppercase">CLIMATE ADAPTATION STRATEGIES</h2>
        <p>Phased approach to climate-proofing your basement</p>
      </div>

      <div class="strategies-grid">
        {adaptationStrategies.map((category) => (
          <div class={`strategy-category ${category.urgency}-priority`}>
            <div class="category-header">
              <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 uppercase">{category.category}</h3>
              <div class={`urgency-badge ${category.urgency}`}>
                <i class={`fa-solid ${
                  category.urgency === 'high' ? 'fa-bolt' :
                  category.urgency === 'medium' ? 'fa-clock' :
                  'fa-calendar'
                }`}></i>
                <span>{category.urgency.toUpperCase()} PRIORITY</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="strategies-list">
              {category.strategies.map((strategy) => (
                <div class="strategy-card border-2 border-slate-200">
                  <h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 uppercase">{strategy.title}</h4>
                  <p class="strategy-description">{strategy.description}</p>
                  <div class="strategy-metrics">
                    <div class="cost">
                      <i class="fa-solid fa-dollar-sign"></i>
                      <span>Cost: {strategy.cost}</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="roi">
                      <i class="fa-solid fa-chart-line"></i>
                      <span>ROI: {strategy.roi}</span>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              ))}
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Infrastructure Challenges -->
  <section class="infrastructure-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold text-slate-900 uppercase">INFRASTRUCTURE CHALLENGES</h2>
        <p>How aging systems struggle with climate change</p>
      </div>

      <div class="infrastructure-grid">
        {infrastructureChallenges.map((system) => (
          <div class="infrastructure-card border-2 border-slate-200">
            <div class="system-header">
              <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 uppercase">{system.system}</h3>
              <div class="capacity-indicator">
                <span class="current-capacity">{system.currentCapacity}</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="challenge-description">
              <h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 uppercase">CHALLENGE:</h4>
              <p>{system.challenge}</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="impact-description">
              <h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 uppercase">BASEMENT IMPACT:</h4>
              <p>{system.impact}</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="timeline-info">
              <i class="fa-solid fa-clock"></i>
              <span>{system.timeline}</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Government Programs -->
  <section class="government-programs">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold text-slate-900 uppercase">GOVERNMENT SUPPORT PROGRAMS 2024-2025</h2>
        <p>Available funding for climate adaptation projects</p>
      </div>

      <div class="programs-grid">
        {governmentPrograms.map((program) => (
          <div class="program-card border-2 border-slate-200">
            <div class="program-header">
              <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 uppercase">{program.program}</h3>
              <div class="coverage-amount">
                <i class="fa-solid fa-dollar-sign"></i>
                <span>{program.coverage}</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="eligibility">
              <h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 uppercase">ELIGIBILITY:</h4>
              <p>{program.eligibility}</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="includes">
              <h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 uppercase">COVERS:</h4>
              <ul>
                {program.includes.map((item) => (
                  <li>
                    <i class="fa-solid fa-check"></i>
                    {item}
                  </li>
                ))}
              </ul>
            </div>
            
            <div class="deadline">
              <i class="fa-solid fa-calendar-times"></i>
              <span>Deadline: {program.deadline}</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>

      <div class="programs-cta">
        <div class="cta-content">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 uppercase">MAXIMIZE YOUR GOVERNMENT SUPPORT</h3>
          <p>We help you navigate all available programs and maximize your rebates and funding opportunities.</p>
          <button class="btn-primary">
            <i class="fa-solid fa-phone"></i>
            Get Funding Consultation: 437-545-0067
          </button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Climate Success Stories -->
  <section class="climate-testimonials">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold text-slate-900 uppercase">CLIMATE ADAPTATION SUCCESS STORIES</h2>
        <p>Toronto homeowners who prepared for climate change</p>
      </div>

      <div class="testimonials-grid">
        {climateTestimonials.map((testimonial) => (
          <div class="testimonial-card climate border-2 border-slate-200">
            <div class="testimonial-header">
              <img src={testimonial.image} alt={testimonial.name} class="customer-avatar" / width="800" height="600" loading="lazy" decoding="async">
              <div class="customer-info">
                <h3 class="customer-name">{testimonial.name}</h3>
                <div class="customer-meta">
                  <span class="customer-location">
                    <i class="fa-solid fa-location-dot"></i>
                    {testimonial.location}
                  </span>
                  {testimonial.verified && (
                    <span class="verified-badge">
                      <i class="fa-solid fa-circle-check"></i>
                      Verified
                    </span>
                  )}
                </div>
                {testimonial.profession && (
                  <div class="profession">
                    <i class="fa-solid fa-user-graduate"></i>
                    <span>{testimonial.profession}</span>
                  </div>
                )}
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="project-info">
              <span class="project-label">Project:</span>
              <span class="project-name">{testimonial.project}</span>
            </div>

            {(testimonial.focus || testimonial.tech) && (
              <div class="special-feature">
                <i class="fa-solid fa-star"></i>
                <span>{testimonial.focus || testimonial.tech}</span>
              </div>
            )}

            <div class="rating">
              {[...Array(5)].map(() => (
                <i class="fa-solid fa-star"></i>
              ))}
            </div>

            <p class="testimonial-content">"{testimonial.content}"</p>

            <div class="testimonial-footer">
              <span class="testimonial-date">{testimonial.date}</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Future-Proof Your Home CTA -->
  <section class="future-proof-cta">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="cta-wrapper">
        <div class="cta-content">
          <div class="cta-icon">
            <i class="fa-solid fa-shield-alt"></i>
          </div>
          <div class="cta-text">
            <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold text-slate-900 uppercase">FUTURE-PROOF YOUR HOME AGAINST CLIMATE CHANGE</h2>
            <p>Don't wait for the next extreme weather event. Climate-adaptive waterproofing protects your basement against today's risks and tomorrow's uncertainties.</p>
            <div class="cta-benefits">
              <div class="benefit">
                <i class="fa-solid fa-check-circle"></i>
                <span>Designed for 2040 climate projections</span>
              </div>
              <div class="benefit">
                <i class="fa-solid fa-check-circle"></i>
                <span>Government rebates up to $15,000</span>
              </div>
              <div class="benefit">
                <i class="fa-solid fa-check-circle"></i>
                <span>Insurance premium reductions</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="cta-action">
            <button class="btn-primary">
              <i class="fa-solid fa-phone"></i>
              Climate Assessment: 437-545-0067
            </button>
            <span class="urgency">Book now - extreme weather season approaching</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <FAQ {faqs} />
  <ContactForm />

  <!-- Resource Images and Diagrams -->
  <ResourceImageGallery resource="drainage-systems" />

</PageLayout>

